<p>The <a href="http://www.goes.noaa.gov/">GOES (Geostationary Satellite)</a> 
provide the commonly seen views of clouds from space.  NOAA is now publishing data from 
these satellites in <a href="http://www.gis.ssd.nesdis.noaa.gov/">GIS formats</a>.  The IEM 
routinely processes some of these files as well as the raw data files provided by our NOAAPort
data feed.

<h3>IEM Processing</h3>

<p>GOES data is routinely available twice an hour (:15 and :45 after the hour). During active
weather situations, the satellites can be placed in rapid-scan mode, which provides more 
frequent updates.  The GIS data available from NOAA only provides the twice per hour files, the
IEM processes the realtime data, which updates as frequently as the data does.

